HEADWORD: Guano
<hw>Gua"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Guanos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Sp. <ets>guano</ets>, fr.
Peruv. <ets>huanu</ets> dung.]</ety> <def>A substance found in great
abundance on some coasts or islands frequented by sea fowls, and
composed chiefly of their excrement. It is rich in phosphates and
ammonia, and is used as a powerful fertilizer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

